Nicaragüenses, Hondureños y Haitianos c #TPS han ayudado a nuestra comunidad #SoFla crecer en diversidad y carácter. Su perdida sería una tragedia para #Miami. Debemos pasar una ley permitiendo q se queden y parar la división de las familias.

I travelled to #Haiti after the earthquake in 2010 and after hurricane Matthew in 2016. So I can personally attest that #Haiti is not prepared to take back nearly 60,000 #TPS recipients under these difficult and harsh conditions.

Nicaraguans, Hondurans, now Haitians. Detained. Deported. They have helped our community grow in diversity and character. Their loss would be a tragedy for Miami. Let’s pass law to stop family divisions.
Tonight's #Haiti #TPS announcement underscores need to pass a legislative solution for those who have been in our nation, working productively to improve their lives + abiding by the rule of law
